Structures are established by city ordinance as approved by city council. Ordinance information is contained in the feature attributes.</abstract>       <purpose>These landmark structure points identify properties that have historically significant designation, entitling them to special tax credits. Additionally these properties are subject to additional design review for any work requiring a permit from the city and county of Denver.</purpose>     </descript>     <status>       <update>As needed</update>     </status>     <spdom>       <bounding>         <westbc>-105.329880</westbc>         <eastbc>-104.886913</eastbc>         <northbc>39.789543</northbc>         <southbc>39.630717</southbc>       </bounding>     </spdom>     <keywords>       <theme>         <themekt>None</themekt>         <themekey>historic</themekey>         <themekey>landmark</themekey>       </theme>       <theme>         <themekt>ISO 19115 Topic Categories</themekt>         <themekey>location</themekey>         <themekey>society</themekey>         <themekey>structure</themekey>       </theme>       <place>         <placekt>None</placekt>         <placekey>Denver</placekey>         <placekey>Denver County</placekey>         <placekey>Colorado</placekey>         <placekey>USA</placekey>       </place>     </keywords>     <accconst>None</accconst>     <useconst>ACCESS CONSTRAINTS:  None.
